  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, to support regression testing, tasks for test evolution have emerged, where the input is a triplet ⟨original method, updated method, original test⟩, and the output is a new test case compatible with the updated method [124].",
    "Other studies explore a natural language-to-test paradigm, taking natural language text (e.g., bug reports) as input and outputting test code to verify it [6,75,110,149].Parallel to task formulation, the composition of fine-tuning datasets is also highly targeted.",
    "Mainstream datasets like Methods2Test offer hundreds of thousands of ⟨focal method, test case⟩ pairs mined from open-source projects to teach general test writing patterns.",
    "To construct larger-scale, cross-language fine-tuning datasets, works such as UniTSyn innovatively leverage the Language Server Protocol (LSP).",
    "By utilizing the \"go-to-definition\" feature, they achieve precise, automated pairing of tested functions and test functions, constructing a massive dataset of 2.7 million samples covering five programming languages [63]."
  ],
